Melocanna baccifera

   [7695.jpg]
    Authority   (Roxb.) Kurz.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 7695

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A evergreen bamboo with single culms arising at a distance of about 60
   cm apart and reaching a height of 10-20 m and a diameter up to 3-7.5
   cm.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial bamboo, flowering after 30-40 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Melocanna.
   FURTHER INF
   This species is native of Bangladesh and Myanmar, where it occurs in
   vast stands, usually on hilly ground. Bamboos grow between the
   latitudes 40°N and S. Though the big bamboo forests usually occur
   between 15-25°N and S.

   Sources
   SOURCES (M. baccifera (Roxb.) Kurz.)
   Hassan M 1988 pp 505-513 [RAIN, TEMP, SAL, DRA, TEXT, PH, DEP]
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 134 [USE]
   Zabala N 1990 pp 164-166 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, LIG, USE]

